# Method Acting Grundkurs
Beginn Mittwoch, 14. Januar 2026
[Sichere dir jetzt einen Kursplatz!](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)
**Du willst:**

¬∑ die Schauspielmethode lernen, die sich in den letzten 100 Jahren weltweit durchgesetzt hat

¬∑ echt, authentisch, glaubw√ºrdig, wahrhaftig, ber√ºhrend und bewegend spielen

¬∑ deinen einzigartigen Weg zur Figur finden

¬∑ dich in Gef√ºhle und Zust√§nde einer Rolle hineinversetzen k√∂nnen

¬∑ deine Atmung und Stimme entwickeln

¬∑ deine K√∂rpersprache in einer motivierten Gruppe von Gleichgesinnten entwickeln

¬∑ organisch die Objektarbeit in dein Schauspiel integrieren

¬∑ lernen, wie man effektiv und effizient Texte auswendig lernt

¬∑ deine mentale St√§rke aufbauen

¬∑ die bew√§hrten Kursunterlagen erhalten und dich von ausgesuchten Videobeispielen inspirieren lassen

¬∑ 24 Stunden praktische Erfahrung sammeln

¬∑ ein Teilnahmezertifikat erhalten

¬∑ von mehr als 40 Jahren Berufserfahrung profitieren

[Dann ist dieser Kurs genau das richtige f√ºr DICH!](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

Und das sagen Teilnehmer*innen:

‚ÄûAuf jeden Fall wird meine Reise bei Dir weiter gehen. Ich bin begeistert, wie Du f√∂rderst und forderst und uns dabei hilfst, den n√§chsten Schritt zu wagen und zu gehen.‚Äú I.

‚ÄûHallo Marco, ich profitiere noch immer von deinem Kurs im Playbacktheater *, in dem ich seit etwa 10 Jahren dabei bin.‚Äú H.

‚ÄûHerzlichen Dank an dich f√ºr den belebenden und lehrreichen Kurs, sowie deine Offenheit.‚Äú E.

‚ÄûMir macht der Method Acting Kurs grosse Freude, die individuelle Arbeit gef√§llt mir sehr.‚Äú S.

‚Äûheute erlebt und umgesetzt. ‚Ä¶ einfach spannend bei dir im unterricht. jedes wort stimmt. danke marco.‚Äú R.

‚ÄûDanke f√ºr den interessanten Kurs. Ich lerne viel und bin auch froh, um die gute Dokumentation, die uns zu Verf√ºgung steht.‚Äú D.

‚Äû√úbrigens, ich habe die Stunde letztes Mal super gefunden ‚Äì ich kam todm√ºde an und ging wacher und selbstbewusster nach Hause. Danke daf√ºr!‚Äú A.

‚ÄûErst mal Danke das Du mich aus der Komfortzone herausgeholt hast, dein Kurs war sehr hilfreich.‚Äú P.

‚ÄûYour training helped, Marco. A teammate told me it was ‚Äûlike real method acting‚Äú. I told them I took method acting. They didn‚Äôt know that when hiring me.‚Äú A.

(Die Testimonials sind aus Datenschutzgr√ºnden anonymisiert. Du willst noch mehr Testimonials? Dann lese auf der [Website](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/) und auf Google weiter.)

Du willst es genau wissen. Auf der Website findest du alles, was du brauchst:

‚Ä¢ Alle [Details](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/) zum Kurs

‚Ä¢ [Testimonials / Bewertungen](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

‚Ä¢ Die [Anmeldung](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

[Was h√§lt dich auf?](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

Kursleitung: Marco Hausammann-Gilardi hat mehr als 40 Jahre Erfahrung als Schauspieler, Autor, Regisseur und Produzent in Theater, Film und Fernsehen. Er war von 1986 bis 1988 an Strasberg‚Äôs Real Stage, bei Ernie Martin (Artistic Director Actor‚Äôs Studio Los Angeles) und am Actor‚Äôs Studio New York (PO). Seit 1988 unterrichtet er auf dieser Basis und seinen praktischen Berufserfahrungen. Er ist Mitglied folgender Berufsverb√§nde:

‚Ä¢ t. Theaterschaffende der Schweiz/Professionnels du spectacle Suisse/Professionisti dello spettacolo Svizzera

‚Ä¢ Verband Filmregie und Drehbuch Schweiz ARF/FDS

‚Ä¢ Verband f√ºr Film- und Fernsehdramaturgie e.V. VeDRA

[ZES Zentrum f√ºr Entwicklung im Schauspiel](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

Das Kompetenzzentrum f√ºr Method Acting

Greetings everyone!

NEW PROJECT JUST IN!  SELF TAPES ARE REQUIRED FOR THIS PROJECT!

Here is what we know/need:

CLIENT:  Blue Ridge Bank

LOCATION:  Richmond VA

DATES:

January 19 - 21 (We do not know which roles will be on which days at this time.  Roles could play multiple days - TBD.  Be sure you are available for all days when submitting.)  Expectation will be 10 hour days per day.

Zoom call backs are expected to be on Thursday, January 15 for talent selected by client.

RATES AND USAGE:

OCP/DAY RATE : $1000.00

OCP : 1 YEAR USE ALL MEDIA (from first air date) : $600.00

20% AGENT : $400.00

TOTAL $2000.00

STILL USE YEAR ALL MEDIA (from first air date) : $400.00

20% AGENCY : $100.00

TOTAL : $500.00

***:30 and :15 LIFT per talent.***

Second Year Option : USE + 10% and 20% Agent Fee (stills and commercials)

***TALENT DOES NOT NEED TO WORK LOCAL, WILLING TO PAY FOR TRAVEL

COSTS.***

ROLES:

SPOT 1: CHEF

ROLE A: Executive Chef, Owner-Operator (Female)

Gender: Female

Age Range: 30‚Äì50

Ethnicity: Open (but should feel authentically ‚Äúlocal owner‚Äù)

Look: Real working chef, confident, capable, warm authority. Not ‚ÄúTV food influencer.‚Äù

Vibe: Smart, composed, witty under pressure. The kind of leader the staff trusts.

Performance Notes: Natural delivery, grounded humor, quick timing on the gentle roast

of the banker.

Wardrobe: Chef coat or elevated kitchen attire, apron optional.

Hands/Action: Comfortable handling food plating, simple kitchen choreography.

ROLE B: Blue Ridge Bank Banker / Treasure Management Officer (BRB TMO)  (Male)

Gender: Male

Age Range: 30‚Äì55

Ethnicity: Person of color preferred, ideally African American (per client request)

Look: Professional, approachable, not stiff. ‚ÄúTrusted advisor‚Äù

Vibe: Helpful, upbeat, coachable, good sport.

Performance Notes: Can take direction, plays ‚Äútrying his best‚Äù in the kitchen without

going broad. Takes pride in his work.

Wardrobe: Business Professional ‚Äì jacket and tie; Apron.

SPOT 2: MECHANIC

ROLE A: Mechanic, Employee (Male)

Gender: Male

Age Range: 25‚Äì30

Ethnicity: Open

Look: Real mechanic energy, hands-on, competent. Not a model in a clean jumpsuit.

Vibe: Straight shooter, likable, confident.

Performance Notes: Conversational, grounded, minimal ‚Äúacting.‚Äù

Wardrobe: Work shirt or mechanic jumpsuit, shop-appropriate layers, subtle grease is

fine.

ROLE B: Blue Ridge Bank Banker / Treasure Management Officer (BRB/TMO) (Male)

Gender: Male

Age Range: 35‚Äì55

Ethnicity: Open, Caucasian preferred

Look: Professional, practical, approachable.

Vibe: Calm problem-solver, earns trust quickly.

Performance Notes: Subtle physical comedy. Earnestly helps with a stuck engine part,

succeeds, then sincerely doesn‚Äôt know what it is. Plays is straight, confident but not

slick.

Wardrobe: Business Professional ‚Äì jacket and tie; Sleeve may be rolled up.

SUBMISSION DETAILS:

Self-tapes are required for consideration.  Please consolidate ALL files into 1 submission and send to [casting@liquidtalentgroup.com](mailto:casting@liquidtalentgroup.com) no later than 5 pm (EST) on Monday, January 12th.  

****All talent should record (3) takes of the scripts providing subtle differences in

performance to show a range of abilities and nuance. Waist up and horizontal filming is

Preferred.  It is preferred talent be off-book for these auditions.  See scripts below****

All talent should slate with:

‚ÄìFirst and last name

‚ÄìRole/Scene

‚ÄìLocation

‚ÄìCurrent height and weight

HERE ARE THE SCRIPTS BY SCENE/ROLE:

SPOT 1 - CHEF:

Open on a Blue Ridge Bank TMO standing next to an executive chef at a top

steak house. Both are working on a dish in front of them.

CHEF (as they prepare a dish): As a chef-owner, I live by reservations and

cash flow. Tom here, from Blue Ridge Bank, has helped me since day one, with

managing my payroll, handling vendor payments, and adding fraud

protection that flags suspicious activity. I can even make deposits without

leaving the restaurant. Yup, Tom keeps me ahead and when I open my next

place, he‚Äôs my first call.

BRB TMO (putting the finishing touches on his attempt at the meal): Voil√†!

CHEF: His plating skills could use some work, though.

BRB TMO: Yes, Chef!

SPOT 2 - GARAGE:

Open on a mechanic in his garage talking to camera, holding a phone. A Blue

Ridge Bank rep is behind him with his hands in the engine.

MECHANIC: My paycheck used to always seem to just disappear.

But the folks at Blue Ridge Bank (He points back to the BRB rep behind him)

really stepped in to help.

MECHANIC (showing their phone): See? Everything I need is right at my

fingertips. My spending, my saving‚Ä¶. They even help me keep track of my

budget.

The BRB TMO rep is pulling and tugging at something in the engine.

MECHANIC: Plus, there‚Äôs no monthly fees or minimum balance requirement.

And my savings actually earn a high interest.

BRB TMO rep (holding up a black box): Is THIS the fuel injector?

MECHANIC (barely looks back): That‚Äôs the fuse box. Great bankers‚Ä¶ not quite

gearheads.

****AGAIN - All talent should record (3) takes of the scripts providing subtle differences in performance to show a range of abilities and nuance. Waist up and horizontal filming is Preferred.  It is preferred talent be off-book for these auditions.****

**++++Doku: Protagonisten gesucht++++**

*Kein Schauspiel-Job, aber vielleicht gibt's ja unter euch Menschen, die noch einen ganz anderen Traum haben...? *

**Bundesweit / Protagonisten (m/f/d), 30 - 50 Jahre f√ºr Doku-Serie, bei der wir Deinen Traum im europ√§ischen Ausland testen / 8 - 14 Drehtage im Mai 2026 / wir zahlen alle Reisekosten, Aufenthalt vor Ort**
 
Du hast einen Traum von einem ganz bestimmten Beruf in einem anderen Land in Europa? Vielleicht wolltest du immer eine Eisdiele in Italien leiten, in Schweden in einem Design-Studio arbeiten oder eine  Strandbar auf Mallorca √ºbernehmen ‚Äì nicht als Urlaub, sondern als echter Arbeitsalltag.

Doch dann kam das Leben dazwischen: Ausbildung oder Studium, ein fester Job. Verantwortung. Sicherheit. Und irgendwann vielleicht auch Familie, Kinder, Verpflichtungen. Pl√∂tzlich ging es nicht mehr nur um dich allein ‚Äì und der Traum r√ºckte immer weiter in den Hintergrund. Aber ganz verschwunden ist er nie. Und der Gedanke daran l√§sst dich immer noch nicht los. Dann melde dich bei uns!

Wir von der Produktionsfirma Picture Punks wollen diesen Traum gemeinsam mit dir testen ‚Äì realistisch, ehrlich und ohne Drehbuch. F√ºr eine Doku-Serie begleiten wir dich dabei, deinen lange gehegten Traum im europ√§ischen Ausland wirklich auszuprobieren. Die Dreharbeiten im Mai 2026 dauern etwa ein bis zwei Wochen. Wir √ºbernehmen alle Reisekosten und k√ºmmern uns um den Aufenthalt vor Ort.

Wichtig ist uns: Du hast einen echten, lange gehegten Traum, keinen spontanen Wunsch. Du willst wissen, ob dieses Leben ‚Äì auch mit Familie, Verantwortung oder Kindern ‚Äì wirklich funktionieren k√∂nnte. Du bist bereit, dich offen auf dieses Experiment einzulassen und du m√∂chtest Teil einer authentischen Doku-Serie sein.

Wir starten mit einem Interview in Deutschland bei Dir zu Hause und begleiten Dich dann √ºber etwa ein bis zwei Wochen ins Ausland, w√§hrend Du Deinen Traum testest. Und wir treffen dich sp√§ter zu Hause noch mal wieder, wenn du am Ende ein Fazit ziehst: War es so sch√∂n, wie Du es Dir immer vorgestellt hast? W√§re das ein Leben f√ºr immer? Oder bist Du froh, wieder zu Hause zu sein?

Wichtig ist uns, dass es kein Urlaub f√ºr Dich ist, sondern es darum geht, dass Du einen realistischen Einblick in ein anderes Leben. Es geht um eine Arbeit im Ausland, die Du hier in Deutschland nicht machen kannst.

Bewerber senden bitte eine E-Mail mit Traumbeschreibung an [info@picturepunks.de](mailto:info@picturepunks.de)

Wir suchen M√ºtter und V√§ter, Menschen mitten im Berufsleben, mit Verantwortung, Alltag und festen Strukturen, die dennoch einen Traum in sich tragen. Du f√ºhlst dich angesprochen? Erz√§hl uns... o Tr√§umst du? info@picturepunks.de fo@picture'

Online Camera Acting Intensive
Film, Television & Digital Media

Galbeni Culture‚Äôs Online Camera Acting Intensive is a professional training program designed for actors who want to confidently work in film, television, commercials, and digital media.

Starting January 19, this intensive offers structured, practical training focused on on-camera performance, audition technique, and the realities of the acting industry.

What You Will Study:
 ‚Ä¢ Camera Acting for Film & Television
 ‚Ä¢ Acting & Scene Study
 ‚Ä¢ Audition Technique for the Camera

 ‚Ä¢ Voice & Speech
 ‚Ä¢ Movement & Improvisation
 ‚Ä¢ Musical Theatre & Singing

Casting Call!!!

(two main characters and a side character)

Tagline - "It fades but we remain "

I'm helping my year friend's group to casting for "The Day Before Yesterday". The film is about a young man suffering from a sudden inability to form new memories attempts to to piece together, with the help of his brother, the day that changed him forever. As he tries to search for answers in the spaces between what he remembers and what he's lost, he discovers fragile connections, forgotten truths and the bittersweet beauty of living everyday as if it were the first. This film will be aimed social media platforms and screened at film festivals.

Personlly, I really want to see this project live because it directed by one of my best talant friends. Please reach to Iris and Milly to show your intrests by sending your profile and showreel in email listed below.

items.text:
CALLING ALL ACTORS For PAID WORK.
We are starting auditions for Give Her My Love, an original drama written by me about life after a breakup. In association with Teal Moon Productions and Stepping Out Theatre Company. 

The show will run for 2 weeks at Barons Court Theatre (2nd - 14th March), London and rehearse in February. Pay will be UK Theatre Agreement rates. 

Auditions will include a self tape round die for January 14th, if that goes well you will sent to an in person recall round later in the month. 

Overview is in the image below, if you meet the casting and would like to inquire further, contact the email address below and you'll be sent the breakdown and sides to tape. 

Best of luck

EPISODE 2 ‚Äî AND THEN THERE WAS‚Ä¶

He checked one name off the list.
Thought it was over.

It wasn‚Äôt.

In Episode 2, the past hits back ‚Äî literally.

After tying up that loose end, @johnwaynesiii (a former mayor preparing a run for U.S. Senate) is run off the road on a snowy night. Accident‚Ä¶ or warning? ‚ùÑÔ∏èüöó

Every problem he fixes reveals another one waiting.
Power has a price.
And the past always collects.

üì¢CASTING CALL

‚ÄúJust Blokes‚Äù, a new piece of Scottish writing by Tori Kay

Water Horse Productions is seeking performers for Just Blokes, a dark comedy exploring men‚Äôs mental health through friendship, masculinity, and the ignorance of youth.

Written by Tori Kay, Artistic Director of Water Horse Productions, and produced by Tori Kay and Zoe Keddie (Co‚ÄìArtistic Director), the production is intended for Edinburgh Festival Fringe 2026.

About the Play‚Ä¶

Just Blokes examines how young men navigate friendship, vulnerability, and emotional responsibility in a culture that often encourages silence. Through humour, sharp dialogue, and moments of discomfort, the play asks how we can better advocate for ourselves and each other.

Genre: Dark Comedy
Themes: Friendship, masculinity, mental health, youth, emotional ignorance

Roles Available‚Ä¶

Four Men (20s) ‚Äì Main Cast
Each character is distinct, flawed, and fully realised, with individual quirks and shortcomings as outlined in the character briefs. Performers should be comfortable with emotionally honest material, fast-paced dialogue, and comedic timing.

Two Women (20s) ‚Äì Supporting Roles
Playing ‚Äúthe girls‚Äù ‚Äî smaller but significant roles that contrast and reflect the blokes‚Äô relationships with women, intimacy, and femininity.

Who We‚Äôre Looking For‚Ä¶

Strong actors with an interest in new writing

Ability to handle dark comedy and sensitive themes with care

Collaborative, open, and thoughtful creatives

Scottish accents welcome but not essential

SUBMISSION DETAILS

Deadline: 31st January 2026

Further details will be provided upon expression of interest

CASTING TWO ROLES - Short Documentary about the Greater Vancouver Food Bank

This Non-Profit project is highlighting the important work that the GVFB is doing for our communities. It will be mostly documentary but we are casting 2 characters to give us a narrative thread that connects some of the services the food bank provides. In a perfect world, we cast a mother with their actual child but we‚Äôre open to casting them separately as well. 

Location: Vancouver/Burnaby
Shoot Dates: Jan 21 & 22 - The mother will be required for both days, the child only one of them (still TBD which day)

Non-Union

Non-speaking role

Any ethnicity welcome to apply

Rate: $400/day

Mother - Age:35-55

Child: - Age 10-15

Please send headshot/reel/resume to: [casting@workshopfilmcompany.com](mailto:casting@workshopfilmcompany.com)

items.text:
Open theatre auditions coming up at The South Devon Players Theatre & Film Company, Brixham

DEVON/ OPEN BOOK PROFITSHARE / THEATRE / ANY GENDER OR ETHNICITY/

- Roles open for actors aged 16 to the sky's the limit. 

- A lot of the roles in our staging of this play  are not bound by gender; we are looking for the strongest actor for each roles. 

- Any ethnicity/ accent/ experience level equally welcome. What we are looking for are great performance skills, pleasant friendly teamwork, and the desire to be an active part of a really excellent quality show. 

- The show is set in 1793. The show is suitable for all audiences. 

- Period costumes made and supplied for all cast. 

- if you cannot make auditions on January 25th please contact us to arrange an audition over the two weeks before. 

- Actors should be based in, or have a base in, Devon because of attending rehearsals and performances. Sorry none of us who are regulars with the theatre team are in a financial or housing position to be able to put people up from further afield. We have a performance in London but have a minibus fundraised for, to get people there and back to Devon. 

- Our show teams are diverse in terms of age, experience, ethnicity and we usually have several neurodivergent team members - everyone coming on board should be willing to work as a part of a diverse group of people. 

- the show is profitshare for funding reasons. We cover rehearsal space/ costumes/ insurance etc by selling second hand bits on eBay and handmade jewellery in a couple of local shops.  This is on an open book process where ticket sales reports and any venue hire costs are shown upfront for perusal, and the ticket profits (Ticket sales less performance venue hire) are shared equally between each person in the show team. Sadly we cannot guarantee how much this is as it can vary wildly as is dependant on ticket sales. We constantly do our best to both promote the show to get those sales as high as possible and to apply for funding to bring everyone up to equity rates but this cant be guaranteed and we don‚Äôt believe in promising what we can‚Äôt guarantee to deliver. 

- ALL cast and crew also are given  access to portfolio photos and show video, copies of any press or promotional content featuring themselves, references on request (after completion of their first show run with us), and anything else that we find we can offer. 

- and - in answer to a common question we get:  nobody is ever charged anything to audition or perform with us.

Do please drop us a line with any questions not answered here or in the downloadable audition resources.

Hi all ‚Äî hope everyone‚Äôs doing well!

I‚Äôm an award-winning acting teacher looking for someone comfortable working inside WordPress using the Themeco Cornerstone builder to help me with a small number of structural edits on my website (mainly heading hierarchy and short text additions).

In exchange, I‚Äôm offering 1‚Äì2 private online acting coaching sessions (my posted rate is usually $150/hour).

If this is something you have experience with and would be interested in, or if you know someone who works with Cornerstone, please feel free to DM me.

P.S. Hope you‚Äôve had a chance to see the new Film Actors Lab 5-minute short film, A Walk in the Park! It‚Äôs already passed 50,000 views in its first month.

Thanks in advance ‚Äî and feel free to share.

www.tedbardy.com

Hi all, happy New Year! I hope this is okay to post here...I am a local actor and recent USC grad looking to update my reel footage, and I wanted to see if there are any other actors out there who would be interested in filming a scene together to use for your reel as well?

I've produced a handful of short films and web series in the past and will happily write a scene based on your character type and provide you with raw and edited footage. I'm hoping to film in the South Denver/Littleton/Centennial area in mid-January (but flexible!) Let me know if you're interested; the best way to get in touch is via email to aspenksomers@gmail.com. TIA!

items.text:
# CASTING CALL: JOIN OUR ACTING PODCAST

When a group of actors sit around a table and use their spoken words to portray characters all going on an adventure together, that's called a tabletop roleplaying game (TTRPG).  Example famous TTRPG podcasts: Critical Role, The Adventure Zone, NADDPod, Dungeons and Daddies, Dimension 20.  Our gaming group plays a variety of tabletop roleplaying games and publishes the audio as a podcast.We react as our character to the scenario presented by the game master. We respond to challenges, overcome obstacles, make jokes and laugh with our fellow acting friends. Would you enjoy acting in-character for a podcast audience? Join us.

# When we play:

Weekends. Flexible times that tend to be in the afternoon and evening, not the morning. Joining us doesn't commit you to every weekend. Instead, we pick games we want to try and sign up for those calendar spots. Members can see who's playing and what ttrpg and pick which sessions they sign up for.

# How long we play / what it‚Äôs like:

Our members sit at their microphones for four hours talking their way through an adventure using their words and laughter to entertain each other. The GM says out loud how far away targets are instead of us all looking at combat maps on a screen. Each player sketches or constructs their own battle map on their desk in front of them, using their own minis. So you'll be able to use your minis every game you play. The recordings are high quality, and we air the audio as a podcast. Don‚Äôt worry, we don‚Äôt publish our names or faces.

# System played:

We get to learn and play a different tabletop roleplaying game (ttrpg) system each session. There‚Äôs no financial burden to you. There isn't any money involved. It's just for fun. The systems are either free to everyone or we were sent a free promotional copy from its creator. That's the perk to being a podcast. By recording and releasing the audio of our game sessions, it means indie game developers get an actual play episode to show their game being actually played. It's why they send us their rules for free. Anyone can listen to and hear an example of their system being played. Actual play episodes help more people see how a game is played, and maybe try it themselves.

# Oneshot or campaign:

Both. Like a traditional campaign, we repeatedly meet familiar non player characters (NPCs), facing challenges and experiencing long term character growth. We play our same character for a year, adapting them to each ttrpg. The characters can‚Äôt tell which dice their players are rolling with. Our characters start at low power in January, grow to epic max fighting strength by December, then retire. Like a oneshot, each individual episode opens with a beginning to its plot, and the exploration of its story ends after four hours.

# Game Mastering (GMing):

We rotate so that everyone is invited to be a player and a game master if they want. The GM gets to pick which ttrpg we play that weekend. If you find a fun ttrpg you want to try, you can sign up as the GM and be confident that there will be players excited to play with you. If you prefer to be a player every time that‚Äôs cool, too. Our members don't have to GM ever if they want a break from it. Getting to pick how often you GM really helps relieve burnout. GM as often as makes you happy.

# You can vibe check past games:

We're on itunes, spotify, youtube, and all the podcast apps. Our cast rotates. Skip around and listen to snippets from a few episodes to see which of our members you want to play with first. The episodes aren't all great, but we have fun together. This isn't a job. It's a hobby, a way to relax and laugh meeting new people who slowly over time become lifelong friends. It's okay to miss games; you aren‚Äôt expected to be present for every session. The opt-in format naturally minimizes table trouble because you can see who‚Äôs signed up to GM and play in a game before you join it, and can pick dates that have people you‚Äôre looking forward to playing with.

# Joining:

The new members tab of FirebreathingKittensPodcast dot com has the full details about our format. To join, email us at FirebreathingKittensPodcast at gmail dot com and tell us about your equipment. Our minimum requirement is 24 bit audio (not 16 bit). If you don‚Äôt know what 24 bit audio means that‚Äôs not a problem. The new members tab of FirebreathingKittensPodcast dot com has an equipment section that explains what all the microphone words mean with pictures and videos. We reply to all emails within three days. Minimum age 21 years old. All experience levels are welcome. We will guide you through character creation and train you how to record great audio.

Please find the latest released `Mutterings' episode - hope you enjoy it!

It's been awhile since our last `Mutterings' offering. 

The Black Comedy series written by Chris Brake are self contained story monologues and all can be watched and are available on the LST Studios YouTube channel.

"Mutterings ‚Äúa privately expressed complaint or expression of dissatisfaction‚Äù The versatile Sophia Harding performs her second monologue in the series `Neighbourhood Watch'.

Jeffery Management Agency ‚Äî Re-Opening for Film Talent Representation! üé¨
We‚Äôre thrilled to announce that Jeffery Management Agency is officially re-opening its books for film-focused actor representation.
For over a decade, Jeffery Management has been recognised on Spotlight as an established talent agency ‚Äî working with professional performers and connecting them with meaningful industry opportunities across screen and stage. 
üîé Who we‚Äôre looking for:
Actors who already have an active Spotlight account and are serious about building a career in feature film ‚Äî not just gigs, cinematic careers with intentional strategy and long-term projects.
We are not a generalist agency. No commercials, no social media hustle, no theatre-only reps. We exist to champion film talent ‚Äî with precision, industry insight, and real momentum.
If you‚Äôre ready to level up ‚Äî and you‚Äôve got the Spotlight profile to prove you‚Äôre playing in the right league ‚Äî we want to hear from you.
üì© How to reach us:
Drop us a message through Fcebook or email info@jefferymanagement.co.uk, and let‚Äôs talk about how we can help you navigate your next cinematic chapter.
Let‚Äôs make films.
Let‚Äôs make careers.
Let‚Äôs do it the right way. üé•‚ú®
For now, this is only open to actors based in the UK.

The world is building. The universe is growing. üåôü™Ñ
Currently, three episodes are available to watch on Studio Lampone‚Äôs YouTube channel and Roku TV:

üéÑ Episode 3: A Very Scary Witchmas

Hocus Pocus is a broad and magical category, and Studio Lampone continues to stand firmly on authenticity ‚Äî authentic casting, dynamic performances, and unique, original screenplays.

üèÜ The series has been nominated for over 150 awards, spanning 2025 into 2026, and we‚Äôre beyond grateful for the recognition.

Now‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs your turn to be part of this marvelous universe. ‚ú®

We are currently seeking little people for upcoming roles. Our goal is to be as inclusive and authentic as possible while creating characters that are unique, dynamic, and pivotal to the story. We truly want to involve and represent the community in a meaningful way.

If you are ‚Äî or know someone who fits this description and would be interested in discussing further ‚Äî all the information can be found on the casting poster. We‚Äôd be more than happy to fill you in on all the spooky, scary, and incredible details. üëªüé¨

ü™Ñ It‚Äôs your lucky day.

Gods and warriors collide in this modern retelling of history‚Äôs greatest battle. At the intimate Lyric Hyperion, a war-weary poet tells us the story of our fascination with war and asks the question: how do you know when you‚Äôve won? 

Starring Madison Uphoff and directed by Morgan McKinnis, AN ILIAD conquers the Lyric Hyperion on January 23 and 24.

Stick around after the performance for craft drinks and to connect with fellow LA artists and theater-goers.

Tickets on sale now on Eventbrite: [http://bit.ly/49NLp3R](http://bit.ly/49NLp3R)

items.text:
Open theatre auditions coming up at The South Devon Players Theatre & Film Company, Brixham

DEVON/ OPEN BOOK PROFITSHARE / THEATRE / ANY GENDER OR ETHNICITY/

- Roles open for actors aged 16 to the sky's the limit. 

- A lot of the roles in our staging of this play  are not bound by gender; we are looking for the strongest actor for each roles. 

- Any ethnicity/ accent/ experience level equally welcome. What we are looking for are great performance skills, pleasant friendly teamwork, and the desire to be an active part of a really excellent quality show. 

- The show is set in 1793. The show is suitable for all audiences. 

- Period costumes made and supplied for all cast. 

- if you cannot make auditions on January 25th please contact us to arrange an audition over the two weeks before. 

- Actors should be based in, or have a base in, Devon because of attending rehearsals and performances. Sorry none of us who are regulars with the theatre team are in a financial or housing position to be able to put people up from further afield. We have a performance in London but have a minibus fundraised for, to get people there and back to Devon. 

- Our show teams are diverse in terms of age, experience, ethnicity and we usually have several neurodivergent team members - everyone coming on board should be willing to work as a part of a diverse group of people. 

- the show is profitshare for funding reasons. We cover rehearsal space/ costumes/ insurance etc by selling second hand bits on eBay and handmade jewellery in a couple of local shops.  This is on an open book process where ticket sales reports and any venue hire costs are shown upfront for perusal, and the ticket profits (Ticket sales less performance venue hire) are shared equally between each person in the show team. Sadly we cannot guarantee how much this is as it can vary wildly as is dependant on ticket sales. We constantly do our best to both promote the show to get those sales as high as possible and to apply for funding to bring everyone up to equity rates but this cant be guaranteed and we don‚Äôt believe in promising what we can‚Äôt guarantee to deliver. 

- ALL cast and crew also are given  access to portfolio photos and show video, copies of any press or promotional content featuring themselves, references on request (after completion of their first show run with us), and anything else that we find we can offer. 

- and - in answer to a common question we get:  nobody is ever charged anything to audition or perform with us.

Do please drop us a line with any questions not answered here or in the downloadable audition resources.

items.text:
I‚Äôm currently casting for an UK Equity short film via Spotlight. This is not my first time casting, but it has been a while (submissions are closed FYI, please don‚Äôt message me about it).

We received 940 submissions for two roles. Quite overwhelming. Understandable given our industry right now. Only 200 of subs were from self-repped actors, which surprised me given it was sent to all.

Giving each submission just one minute of attention is nearly 17 hours without a break. Days of work. When numbers are this high, long listing is about finding easy reasons to say yes / no.

I had to quickly reduce 940 to around 200. And then the director and I created a long list of 40 who were invited tape. 14 of which declined to tape / were unavailable. I would love to give feedback to actors individually on why they didn‚Äôt progress, sometimes it‚Äôs something so simple to rectify. But there‚Äôs just no time.

This most recent foray into casting has really given me some insight that will shape how I think about my own acting CV and representation. I wonder if my experience might help others in a very broad sense, because I was honestly shocked by how basics were not being met, by performers, and also agents.

I‚Äôm considering doing some sort of social media series to explain what made people stand out at various stages, and more crucially what basic things might be corrected.

If this is something you‚Äôre interested in, or you want to stay updated, you are welcome to follow me on Instagram. I am easy to find. I will be casting more projects in 2026, including my own work.

Happy New Year everyone. I‚Äôve seen so much talent over the past few weeks, please know that even if you didn‚Äôt tape for me, I looked carefully at every single CV I was sent, and will remember those who stood out.

topComments.text:
Insight is always appreciated üëç
Back in the late 1990‚Äôs I was working with a touring theatre company and in my third season with them was given the opportunity to direct a production of The Tempest, and was involved in the casting process for that and the company‚Äôs other production of As You Like It.

During that I gained a huge insight into my own practices and choices as an actor, from application to presentation to performance.

I took a break from the industry in 2010 when I got married and chose a different, and frankly more financially stable, industry until my daughter was older.

It wasn‚Äôt a hard choice to make, my career path had been narrowing down for awhile at that stage, but I was eventually nudged back into the industry.

Everything was different, instead of printed cv‚Äôs and (expensive to reproduce) 8x10 headshots, all applications were made online, my then 14 year old daughter was having to show me how to operate a computer.

Spotlight was different, no longer these great tomes that one could peruse in order to find a (overpriced) photographer for your headshots and hope that a casting director went to when they needed a new face, but an opportunity to profile oneself and direct appropriate jobs directly to one‚Äôs email.

Any and all insight into improving my search for work is always welcome.

I have a very good agent who regularly communicates with me, the best that I‚Äôve ever had.

I‚Äôm still ambitious, I‚Äôm still struggling to make ends meet, but I‚Äôm happy and healthy as I approach my 60th birthday in the autumn of 2026.

I‚Äôll follow you on instagram üëç

Thanks for posting this. An interesting post, which reminds me just how competitive this industry is. I‚Äôd be interested to know the playing ages of the roles you were casting. I was surprised to read that a large number declined to tape. Others could have had the opportunity. Also that the basics were ignored - presumably these were self tape instructions etc. The industry is so very competitive and it is increasingly difficult to book jobs, but the least we can ALL (whatever our individual role in the process) do is be professional, communicate well, submit self tapes on time, be clear with instructions, follow instructions etc. That is the job and I‚Äôve heard many say that we should view the audition as an acting job in itself. By the way, I‚Äôm following you on IG.

I‚Äôm currently casting for an UK Equity short film via Spotlight. This is not my first time casting, but it has been a while (submissions are closed FYI, please don‚Äôt message me about it).

We received 940 submissions for two roles. Quite overwhelming. Understandable given our industry right now. Only 200 of subs were from self-repped actors, which surprised me given it was sent to all.

Giving each submission just one minute of attention is nearly 17 hours without a break. Days of work. When numbers are this high, long listing is about finding easy reasons to say yes / no.

I had to quickly reduce 940 to around 200. And then the director and I created a long list of 40 who were invited tape. 14 of which declined to tape / were unavailable. I would love to give feedback to actors individually on why they didn‚Äôt progress, sometimes it‚Äôs something so simple to rectify. But there‚Äôs just no time.

This most recent foray into casting has really given me some insight that will shape how I think about my own acting CV and representation. I wonder if my experience might help others in a very broad sense, because I was honestly shocked by how basics were not being met, by performers, and also agents.

I‚Äôm considering doing some sort of social media series to explain what made people stand out at various stages, and more crucially what basic things might be corrected.

If this is something you‚Äôre interested in, or you want to stay updated, you are welcome to follow me on Instagram. I am easy to find. I will be casting more projects in 2026, including my own work.

Happy New Year everyone. I‚Äôve seen so much talent over the past few weeks, please know that even if you didn‚Äôt tape for me, I looked carefully at every single CV I was sent, and will remember those who stood out.

üé¨ Seeking Post-Production Collaborators for Student Film ‚Äì ‚ÄúTherapist‚Äù

Hi everyone! I‚Äôve been putting off this project for almost a year, but I‚Äôm ready to bring it to life. I‚Äôm looking for talented post-production artists to join me on Therapist, a student film, and gain hands-on experience on a real project with festival potential. This is your chance to collaborate from start to finish, work with a passionate creative team, and add a professional credit to your portfolio.

Synopsis:
After a suicide attempt, Javier is admitted to a mental health facility under the care of Dr. Chamberlain, a psychiatrist he has trusted for years. There, he meets Aiden, an energetic patient who suspects the doctor is hiding something. Determined to prove Aiden wrong, Javier digs deeper and uncovers unsettling truths that challenge everything he thought he knew.

Therapist, written, directed, and edited by Alexis Gautreau, is a psychological drama and thriller exploring trust, deception, and the dangers lurking where we least expect them.

Project Vision:
I already have a YouTube link showing what the project looks like so far, but I believe we can make it even better, maybe even terrifying. I‚Äôm still deciding if this will be my final cut. My goal is to submit the film to film festivals, and it has huge potential. I can‚Äôt achieve this without a strong, dedicated post-production team.

Roles We‚Äôre Looking For:
üéµ Composer / Music Designer ‚Äì create original score or soundtrack
üéô Dialogue Editor ‚Äì clean up background noise, separate overlapping audio, and polish clarity. I can provide a tool or website to assist
üîä Sound Designer ‚Äì enhance sound effects and ambience using existing material
üéß Foley Artist ‚Äì add practical or creative sounds to existing footage
üéö Re-Recording / Mixing Engineer ‚Äì balance dialogue, music, and effects for the final mix
üé® Colorist ‚Äì finalize color and overall look of the film
‚ú® VFX / Motion Graphics / Image Retouching ‚Äì edit images, remove objects, add graphics or minor visual effects

Collaboration Details:
 ‚Ä¢ This is a fully collaborative project from start to finish
 ‚Ä¢ Work will be conducted via Zoom meetings
 ‚Ä¢ Some sound assets are available through Splice, which I already have

How to Apply:
Submit examples of your work to my email: algautre@my.loyno.edu. Include relevant experience or samples for the role you‚Äôre interested in. Feel free to also DM me with any questions.

This is a rare opportunity to gain hands-on experience, collaborate with a global team, and have your work credited on a film with festival potential. It‚Äôs a lot of work to do alone, so I need all hands on deck. Let‚Äôs make something incredible together!

Please share this with your friends and family.

NYC STUDENT FILM CASTING CALL

Hi! I'm looking for two male actors and two drag queens to act as supporting roles for my senior thesis film called TUG. The film centers around a lesbian and her relationship with the drag queen she's documenting.

Roles:

**Jake Bison**: Supporting. 20s. Oblivious. Helpful. Youngest Brother. Sara‚Äôs right hand man and the lead‚Äôs, Max‚Äôs, helping hand. He is overwhelmed by being the only straight man in the vicinity during all shoots. His goal is to get on Max‚Äôs good side and her nerves.

**Queen #2**: Supporting. 20s-30s. Drag Queen. Comedic. Honest. She is the comedic relief full of puns and stories to make an awkward moment looser. She doesn‚Äôt take herself seriously and is simply along for the ride with no desire to have a deeper understanding of the others.

**Queen #3**: Supporting. 20s. Drag Queen. Quiet. KInd. Less Experienced. She is there to show the younger community of drag and lets her inexperienced career dictate the lack of words she speaks.

**Random Man**: Cameo. 20s. Not memorable. Cool. Probably high. No one is sure how he got there. He‚Äôs a random partygoer who‚Äôs there for the free drinks, the chicks and the guys. He definitely played a sport in college and always brings it up when drunk.

Shoot Dates: Jan 18th - 25th (specific dates sent upon request)

Pay: Unpaid, meals and snacks provided.

**üé¨ CASTING CALL: *****Illusions of Grandeur ***

******Live Action******

*A Short Film by *Jordan Jackson

**Genre: Drama / Coming-of-Age**

**Tone: Gritty realism with a child‚Äôs imaginative lens**

**COMPENSATION: Unpaid :( , Lunch, Copy of Footage **

**Filming Dates: End of January or Early February **

***Please Submit by January 20th, 2025 :)**

**[EMAIL jjacks24@uccs.edu FOR SIDES]**

**LOCATION: Colorado Springs **

**Logline:**

A young boy‚Äôs love for his superhero idol blurs with reality when he discovers his hero ‚Äî and his father ‚Äî isn‚Äôt the savior he imagined.

**üß¢ JOEY (6‚Äì12)**
**Description:** Innocent, imaginative, and full of heart. Joey escapes his unstable home through superhero fantasies. He believes good always wins ‚Äî even when the world around him says otherwise.
**Type:** Young actor capable of conveying wonder, playfulness, and heartbreak.

**üåπ ELISE (16‚Äì20)**
**Description:** Joey‚Äôs older sister and reluctant guardian. She‚Äôs grown up too fast ‚Äî sharp, tired, protective. She carries both resentment and love for her family‚Äôs situation.
**Tone:** Grounded realism, emotional restraint with underlying warmth.

**üïØÔ∏è JOEY‚ÄôS MOM (Late 20s‚Äì30s)**
**Description:** Overworked and emotionally exhausted. Trying to hold her family together while fighting her own quiet collapse. Her phone calls reveal more than she ever tells her children.
**Type:** Actor who can express fatigue, vulnerability, and quiet strength.

**ü•Ä GENTLEMAN PERFECT / JAMES (30s‚Äì40s)**
**Description:** Once a man of pride and potential ‚Äî now homeless, addicted, and haunted by his past. In Joey‚Äôs eyes, he‚Äôs a superhero; in reality, he‚Äôs a fallen one. A tragic, layered role requiring depth, subtlety, and broken charisma.
**Tone:** Complex mix of dignity, shame, and fading hope.

**üóùÔ∏è HOMELESS MAN (40s‚Äì50s)**
**Description:** A street survivor who represents the darker side of desperation. Not evil, but lost. Brief appearance, but a pivotal moment showing Joey‚Äôs innocence colliding with danger.

**üíî YOUNG MAN / MUGGER (18‚Äì22)**
**Description:** A mirror of what Joey could become ‚Äî young, broke, trying to survive. His confrontation with Gentleman Perfect reveals both the world‚Äôs cruelty and the man‚Äôs lingering morality.

**üíÑ WOMAN (20s‚Äì30s)**
**Description:** Victim of the mugging; small role but emotionally grounding. Her scene reinforces Joey‚Äôs belief that Gentleman Perfect is still a hero ‚Äî just before that belief unravels.

**üë¨ ERIC (18‚Äì22)**
**Description:** Joey‚Äôs friend ten years later. Provides contrast and realism ‚Äî he wasn‚Äôt there to see the ‚Äúheroics.‚Äù Grounded, observant, a reminder that nostalgia and truth rarely match.

**üåá OLDER JOEY (Late teens‚Äì20s)**
**Description:** Once full of imagination, now hardened by betrayal. Still searching for something heroic in a world that let him down. His closing narration brings the story full circle.

**üìÖ Production Notes**
* **Setting:** Urban neighborhood; mostly night exteriors.
* **Tone:** Visual realism with moments of childhood wonder.
* **Themes:** Hero worship, family, addiction, disillusionment, legacy.
* **Shooting Length:** 10‚Äì12 pages (~10‚Äì15 minutes).

CASTING CALL - Unpaid Independent Short Film.

TITLE: Ringer

**Production Type:** Independent Short Film

**Location:** Arvada, Northglenn, Colorado.

**Compensation:** Unpaid

**Union Status:** Non-Union

**Filming Window:** End of March

LOGLINE: A Manic pixie Dream Girl type plot goes south when the characters become aware that they're in a movie.

GENRE: Horror

ROLES:

CRAIG - (Male, 20s): A very down to earth and relatable guy, who has a special interest in music, but is also somewhat shy at times and will hesitate before speaking up for himself.

DECEMBER - (Female, 20s): A quirky manic pixie dream girl, who loves filmmaking, especially really old films from the 30s - 50s, and appears very happy and bubbly, but holds a darker side when she begins to questions the things around her.

SOPHIE - (Female, 20s): A punk rock tomboy who appears tough on the surface, but has a soft side underneath. While she has suffered through past trauma, she doesn‚Äôt stop it from letting her care about any of her friends.

NOTE: We are especially looking for actors who can do great improv and can play the character, and a fictionalized version of themselves. 

TO SUBMIT: Please email at alecopedia@gmail.com with a message saying you are interested and the subject line, ‚ÄúRinger Audition - [INSERT ACTOR NAME]‚Äù. From there you will be given a link to a folder, where you may submit your Headshot, Resume, and Reel, along with an Audition Side of each character you want to audition for.

DEADLINE: Friday, January 16th

Hello everyone,

 

Join the one and only Mark Winstanley for a 4-week online course: Playing with Life's Gestures

 

Mark is an inspirational teacher who has taught at some of the most prestigious theatre and acting schools in the world, including the √âcole Philippe Gaulier, the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art (RADA), and East 15 Acting School.

** **

*"A playful provocateur, he guides his students towards discovering their unique sense of pleasure, presence, and freedom in performance"*

 

Over the four weeks you will study the language of gesture and movement as a pathway to creative freedom.

 

Every Tuesday between the 3rd of February and the 24th of February on Zoom between 7pm and 9pm (UK time).

 

This workshop is open to anyone wanting to dig further into their acting practice.

 

Pay what you can, we suggest ¬£80 for the whole course.

 

Email us to register your interest on theperformersplayground@gmail.com or book here: https://www.theperformersplayground.com/online-course

This wonderful workshop with Suzie Ferguson (formally Director of Hearts and Minds Clown Doctors in Scotland) is a process of discovery that invites you to connect with your authenticity and playfulness, to discover how you can be more yourself, more truthful in a moment of connection with other people.

You don‚Äôt need a clowning background, just curiosity, openness, and a readiness to be active in exploring what connection means for you. It is open to anyone who connects with others in their work: teachers, directors, therapists, priests, health workers, those who work in music, art and theatre, as well as clowns who work in social/therapeutic contexts. 
This process is experienced practically through guided exercises, working alone, in pairs and as a group. It is not about finding your clown or refining a performance piece; it is about helping you find what you need to learn about connection for your practice.
Suzie teaches Applied Clowning, a form of clowning that extends beyond the stage, into the world.
Suzie works internationally and is well-loved for her practical, supportive and freeing approach to teaching therapeutic clowning with participants from varied professional backgrounds.

Pfarrer Nils Petrat parkt sein gelbes Checker Taxi in K√∂ln und stellt uns eine Frage, die in einer globalisierten, oft un√ºbersichtlichen Welt pl√∂tzlich wieder √ºberall auftaucht: Was bedeutet Heimatbewusstsein heute, und wie stehst Du zu Patriotismus, Nationalstolz und diesem sp√ºrbaren Heimattrend? 

In dieser Folge sind Sandra und ich, Christian, als exklusive Interviewpartner dabei. Ich formuliere es bewusst so, wie es viele Menschen f√ºhlen, aber selten sauber aussprechen: 

In einem gesunden Ma√ü, ohne Gewalt, ohne Hass, ohne √úberh√∂hung, kann Nationalstolz und Patriotismus etwas sein, das Halt gibt. F√ºr mich geh√∂rt das Wissen, woher man kommt, zu den Grundbed√ºrfnissen des Menschen. Es geht um Zugeh√∂rigkeit, und genau deshalb spielen Menschen, Gruppen, Orte, kulturelle G√ºter, religi√∂se Werke und Feste eine zentrale Rolle. Das kann etwas Kostbares sein, etwas, das man sichtbar pflegt, nicht als Kampfansage, sondern als Ausdruck von Wertsch√§tzung. 

Spannend wird es dort, wo Heimat nicht nur als Ort verstanden wird, sondern als innerer Zustand. Als Christ hat Heimat f√ºr mich vor allem eine innere Dimension: ein seelisches Zuhause, ein innerer Hafen. Und genau hier entsteht der eigentliche Konflikt unserer Zeit, denn viele Debatten behandeln Heimat wie ein reines Au√üen, Flagge, Symbol, Folklore. Dabei geht es im Kern um Bindung, Sinn, Sicherheit, Gemeinschaft und Identit√§t. 

Wenn man das √ºbersieht, versteht man auch nicht, warum Menschen so emotional reagieren, wenn das Thema Heimat in Schlagzeilen, Talkshows oder Social Media auftaucht.

Zuschauerfrage am Ende: Was bedeutet Heimatbewusstsein f√ºr Dich ganz pers√∂nlich, und wo verl√§uft Deine Grenze zwischen gesundem Stolz und gef√§hrlicher Ideologie? 

Gef√§llt dir das Video, dann abonniere den Kanal, aktiviere die Glocke und gib dem Video einen Daumen nach oben, damit mehr Menschen sachlich mitdiskutieren.
